b'To our servicemembers and veterans struggling with mental health challenges, and their loved ones: we are here for you. - Joe'
b'Throughout Sept. we will recognize #SuicidePreventionMonth, but this is an issue it demands our attention every day of the year. -Joe'
b'We must do more to help prevent military and veteran suicides. - Joe'
b'There is no single solution that ends suicide. -Joe'
b'I urge Congress to come together on a final defense bill that can be sent to the President and signed into law. - Joe'
b'It expands the availability of PAs to provide mental health care evaluations and services for servicemembers and their families. -Joe'
b'This year, the final provision of my bipartisan #CarePackage passed the Senate as part of #NDAA - Joe'
b'\xe2\x80\xa6so these services reach the troops and veterans who need them most. -Joe'
b'We need to ensure the laws we\xe2\x80\x99ve passed, including the #SextonAct & #CarePackage, are implemented correctly - Joe'
b'& to deliver mental health care in a way that meets the unique needs of servicemembers and veterans\xe2\x80\xa6 -Joe'
b'\xe2\x80\xa6which helped expand access to quality mental health care for servicemembers - Joe'
b'last year, we had provisions of my bipartisan Servicemember and Veterans Mental Health #CarePackage signed into law -Joe'
b'& established\xe2\x80\xa6a requirement that every servicemember \xe2\x80\x93 Active, Guard & Reserve \xe2\x80\x93 receive an annual mental health assessment. - Joe'
b'In 2014, my bipartisan Jacob Sexton Military Suicide Prevention Act was signed into law. -Joe'
b'Despite gridlock in Congress, this is an issue where we have a solid bipartisan consensus. - Joe'
b'These numbers illustrate the simple, terrible fact that we are losing too many of our servicemembers and veterans to suicide. -Joe'
b'We are painfully aware of the statistic that an estimated 20 veterans a day take their own lives. - Joe'
b'In 2015, 475 servicemembers took their own lives. Prior to that we lost 443 servicemembers in 2014 and 474 servicemembers in 2013. -Joe'
b'Last year, for the fourth straight year, more U.S. troops were lost to suicide than in combat. - Joe'
